<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1937] Add convenience method to Result for obtaining the timestamp of a column</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1937</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From Doug Meil on list:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to suggest a convenience method on Result for getting the timestamp of a value if it hasn&apos;t already been suggested before.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Getting the value is easy from a Result instance...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;      byte b[] = r.getValue( Bytes.toBytes(&quot;family&quot;), Bytes.toBytes(&quot;qualifier&quot;) );&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;... but getting the timestamp from KeyValue is a little tedious...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;      KeyValue kv[] = r.raw();&lt;br/&gt;
      for (int j = 0; j &amp;lt; kv.length; j++) {&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            String col = Bytes.toString( kv&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;j&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.getColumn() ) );&lt;br/&gt;
            // make sure you get the timestamp from the right column, etc etc.&lt;br/&gt;
            long ll = kv&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;j&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.getTimestamp();&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(etc...)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is it reasonable to have something like...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;      long = r.getTimestamp( family, qualifier );&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
