                            <comment id="12770075" author="streamy" created="Mon, 26 Oct 2009 16:16:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Right now there are two primary ways to get data out of a Result.  You either grab the KVs and iterate them directly, or you use one of the NavigableMaps.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem with the Maps are that they end up only containing a portion of the data for each endpoint (for example, after getting to the value as Doug describes, we can&apos;t determine the timestamp).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe we could add a few methods like Result.getKeyValues(...) that returned a subset of the total KVs, but would make more sense to someone and be easier to deal with in clients.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;// Return all keys in the specified family
KeyValue [] kvs = result.getKeyValues(family);

// Return all versions of the specified column
KeyValue [] kvs = result.getKeyValues(family, qualifier);

// Iterate versions of the column
for(KeyValue kv  : kvs) {
  byte [] value = kv.getValue();
  long stamp = kv.getTimestamp();
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12917119" author="ryanobjc" created="Sat, 2 Oct 2010 00:07:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a proposal of an enhanced API here:  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3073&quot; title=&quot;New APIs for Result, faster implementation for some calls&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3073&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3073&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;  which covers this case by allowing people to get KeyValue for a column w/o dealing with the raw() interface directly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918235" author="streamy" created="Tue, 5 Oct 2010 21:47:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unclear whether we still need this JIRA considering new one by ryan.  Punting to 0.92 for now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918244" author="ryanobjc" created="Tue, 5 Oct 2010 22:00:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3073&quot; title=&quot;New APIs for Result, faster implementation for some calls&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3073&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3073&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; will fix this issue, because users will be able to obtain KeyValue.  I&apos;ll update this when I commit the other.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918382" author="ryanobjc" created="Wed, 6 Oct 2010 01:44:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The call:  Result.getColumn() and Result.getColumnLatest() which return a list of KeyValue and a KeyValue respectively is now available.  Once the user has the KeyValue they can access the timestamp, the rowid, the qualifier and every subfield, including value.  &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
